main event: The document contains reports and investigations related to a mysterious object found in the Frick Park area of Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania on 15 September 1959, described as a conically shaped object with peculiar components.
interesting points: The object was reported to be made of polyethylene plastic, yellow in color, and had a circuit consisting of a light bulb, battery, antenna, and various other items, arranged in a seemingly haphazard manner.
The object was discovered near the site of a reported explosion, and attempts to open it were unsuccessful, leading to speculation about its purpose and origin.

The weight of the object was about twelve pounds, and it was not found to have any airborne capability, leading to the conclusion that it may have been part of a prank or a school experiment, possibly due to the beginning of the school term.

The investigation involved the assistance of various military and technical intelligence centers, including a preliminary investigation by the Air Defense Command Post and evaluations by the Electronic Technology Laboratory and the Aerial Reconnaissance Laboratory of WADC.
Witnesses reported that the object was cone-shaped, had a flashing red light, and was equipped with antenna-like wires and a steel cable, adding to the mystery surrounding its nature and purpose.
sighted object: conically shaped object with peculiar components
witnesses: Pittsburgh police, military personnel, and airport tower operator
photographs: no, the report does not contain photographs
